Pandas built-in visualization¶

We will learn pandas built-in capabilities for data visualization! It's built-off of matplotlib.

Pandas built-in-visualization: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/user_guide/visualization.html
Style sheet Link: https://matplotlib.org/stable/gallery/style_sheets/style_sheets_reference.html
Color maps: https://matplotlib.org/stable/users/explain/colors/colormaps.html#

In [1]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt 
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
%matplotlib inline

Pandas built-in plot¶

Link: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/user_guide/visualization.html

  • df.plot.area
  • df.plot.bar
  • df.plot.density
  • df.plot.hist
  • df.plot.line
  • df.plot.scatter
  • df.plot.bar
  • df.plot.box
  • df.plot.hexbin
  • df.plot.kde
  • df.plot.pie

You can also just call df.plot(kind='hist')

In [47]:
df1.plot(y='B') # default kind='lineplot'
Out[47]:
<AxesSubplot:>

Available kinds are:

-'line' : line plot (default)
- 'bar' : vertical bar plot
- 'barh' : horizontal bar plot
- 'hist' : histogram
- 'box' : boxplot
- 'kde' : Kernel Density Estimation plot
- 'density' : same as 'kde'
- 'area' : area plot
- 'pie' : pie plot
- 'scatter' : scatter plot
- 'hexbin' : hexbin plot.
In [48]:
df1.plot.scatter(x='A',y='B')
Out[48]:
<AxesSubplot:xlabel='A', ylabel='B'>
In [54]:
plt.style.use('seaborn')
df1.plot(kind='scatter',x='A',y='B',c='D',cmap='coolwarm')
Out[54]:
<AxesSubplot:xlabel='A', ylabel='B'>
In [57]:
#with with changed size (s) of colmun C 

df1.plot(kind='scatter',x='A',y='B',c='D',cmap='coolwarm', s=df1['C']*200)
plt.show()

Hexagonal bin plot¶

For Bivariate Data, alternative to scatterplot:

In [82]:
df1.plot.hexbin(x='A',y='B',gridsize=20,cmap='cool')
Out[82]:
<AxesSubplot:xlabel='A', ylabel='B'>
